resume_dir = "/tmp"

us_citizens = []

pdf_files = [f for f in os.listdir(resume_dir) if f.endswith('.pdf')]

        # Check if the resume mentions US citizenship

        text_lower = text.lower()
        
        if any(phrase in text_lower for phrase in [
            "united states citizen",
            "u.s. citizen",
            "us citizen",
            "american citizen",
            "citizenship: united states",
            "citizenship: u.s.",
            "citizenship: us",
            "citizen of the united states"
        ]):
            # Extract candidate name from filename (remove .pdf extension)
            candidate_name = pdf_file.replace('.pdf', '').replace('_', ' ')
            us_citizens.append(candidate_name)
            print(f"✓ {candidate_name}")
    
    except Exception as e:
        print(f"Error processing {pdf_file}: {e}")

print(f"\nTotal US citizens found: {len(us_citizens)}")
